<TEXT>
a tropical storm warning was issued wednesday for 
islands in the eastern caribbean while a depression moves westward 
from the atlantic forecasters reported 
at 1030 pm edt the center of the depression was near latitude 
166 degrees north and longitude 535 west about 500 miles east of 
the lesser antilles according to the national hurricane center in 
suburban coral gables 
the depression with maximum sustained winds of 35 mph was 
moving westward at about 20 mph and some strengthening is expected 
by thursday afternoon the center reported 
a tropical storm watch has been posted from dominica to the 
british virgin islands 
a us air force reconnaissance plane will be flown thursday to 
investigate the depression 
the depression would become a named storm if maximum sustained 
winds reach 39 mph 
dean the second hurricane of the junetoseptember atlantic 
season died earlier this month in the north atlantic after causing 
minor damage in bermuda 
