southeast of oviedo houses the 18th century statue of the virgin of 
the battlefield or santina patron of asturias 
galicia of which santiago is the capital is providing 165 
million to help pay for the visit and accommodations for the young 
visitors said david cheda provincial government spokesman 
he said the government hoped to recover 40 percent of it from 
fees to food and soft drink concessionaires 
archbishop antonio maria rouco varela of santiago said john 
pauls visit was of decisive importance for the church but did 
not say how much his archbishopric was spending on it 
