a year later mystery still surrounds 
the plane crash that killed president mohammed zia ulhaq us 
ambassador arnold raphel and 28 other people on aug 17 1988 
us and pakistani investigators all but ruled out technical 
failure on the presidential plane a sturdy fourengine lockheed 
c130 turboprop known as pak one 
their report said the most probable cause was a criminal act or 
sabotage but did not say by whom gen zias son speaks of a 
coverup 
the plane climbed into a clear sky over the sutlej river near the 
indian border behaved erratically three minutes later then dived 
into a sandy plain and exploded killing everyone aboard 
in addition to zia and raphel the dead included the us 
military attache and most of zias top military officers 
some pakistanis believe it was an assassination by domestic 
political enemies zia accumulated during 11 years of military rule 
others prefer a foreign motive 
investigators said the explosion and fire obliterated most clues 
but they found residues of chemicals that could if combined be 
used in a detonator 
ghulam ishaq khan president of the senate assumed the 
presidency and declared zia a martyr bolstering the belief that the 
general was murdered 
zias death opened the way three months later for the first 
free elections in more than a decade the opposition pakistan 
peoples party won and its leader benazir bhutto became the first 
woman prime minister in the islamic world 
the uspakistani investigation report parts of which were made 
public said the plane could have been put out of control by 
mechanical or deliberate interference with the flight control 
system interference with cockpit controls disabling of the pilots 
or explosive devices used to achieve one of those results 
a popular theory holds that the six crew members were knocked out 
by traceless nerve gas possibly by someone aboard another says a 
small explosive device damaged some critical part of the flight 
control system 
suspicion fell on four groups 
agents of afghanistans communist government possibly trained 
by the soviet kgb secret police zia with us support was a 
staunch supporter of moslem guerrillas in the neighboring country 
domestic political foes especially those loyal to ms bhutto 
zia overthrew her father zulfikar ali bhutto in a 1977 military 
coup and he was hanged two years later 
pakistans minority shiite moslems because of the assassination 
of their spiritual leader a month earlier 
agents of india the two nations have fought three wars since 
