<TEXT>
the tnt movie breaking point is a remake 
of the 1964 film 36 hours starring james garner and eva marie 
saint 
the question is why 
granted the premise of the world war ii thriller is intriguing 
the nazis capture a us intelligence officer and try to trick him 
into thinking hes in a hospital suffering amnesia and the war is 
over so hell reveal when and where the allied invasion of europe 
is to take place 
but it is certainly dated and no matter how interesting the 
premise the story doesnt work if the viewers dont care what 
happens to the characters as weakly written as they are they 
arent helped by a cast list that is an eery vision of 
weeknightonthedinnertheatercircuit 
breaking point premieres tonight and is repeated saturday and 
sunday 
corbin bernsen who does an admirable job of playing a crass 
shallow divorce lawyer on la law would have been more 
convincing as one of the nazis his maj jefferson pike comes off as 
a vacuous dilettante who looks like hed be much more comfortable 
shopping for sweaters at saks than plotting some nasty old invasion 
of normandy 
the grinding wheels of the plot are set in motion when pike goes 
to an unexplained meeting with a unsavory character at a lisbon bar 
drinks spiked espresso and is plucked off the sidewalk by the nazis 
allowing director peter markle to ignore the plodding script for a 
while and engage in some arty slomo and blackandwhite photography 
after a wee bit of electroshock torture which causes pike to 
grimace and perspire he wakes up in a pleasant rest home surrounded 
by seeming yanks the date on the newspaper is convincing enough 
but pike is suspicious when everyone is vague on the identity of the 
mayor of chicago and who won the world series 
joanna pacula who is making a career of tv world war ii dramas 
crossings escape from sobibor plays anna the german 
nurse enlisted to entice pike into spilling the beans because she 
looks exactly like the wife the nazis have told him is dead no 
wonder she and his wife look alike she plays both of them if not 
for this amazing circumstance the rest of the story would have been 
tragically lost to posterity 
pike aided by the miracle of flashbacks figures out the nazi 
game he confirms his suspicions by tripping anna up with a bit of 
clever dialogue something about a paper cut received recently in 
london aha were supposed to be in occupied germany understand 
this not exactly a battle of wits between two mental giants 
only the stalwart john glover david inspires any interest 
playing gerber the nazi doctor who hatches the brainwashing plot 
as a potential footnote for the annals of bizarre casting the 
preppylooking david marshall grant thirtysomething plays a 
nazi commandant his presence must satisfy some behindthescenes 
debt we arent aware of his only plot purpose seems to be to menace 
the proceedings by expressing whining doubts about the validity of 
dr gerbers experiment not exactly the stuff of razoredged 
suspense 
unlike the 1964 film breaking point ends with a cynical 
twist which might have played on a work of contemporary fiction 
but isnt particularly compelling as part of a historical drama 
most viewers do know we won the war dont they 
despite some wonderfully inane dialogue eg dr gerber you 
wont have to sleep with major pike again nurse anna with 
straight face thank you sir the breaking point for most 
viewers will come about 10 minutes into the film 
